import { useState } from 'react' import Workouts from '../components/Workouts' import NewWorkout from '../components/NewWorkout' import Templates from '../components/Templates' import NewTemplate from '../components/NewTemplate' function Dashboard(props) { const [displayType, setDisplayType] = useState("") const buttonController = (e, type) => { e.preventDefault() setDisplayType(type) switch (displayType){ default: alert(type) return case "Workouts": alert(type) return case "NewWorkout": alert(type) return case "Templates": alert(type) return case "newTemplate": alert(type) return } } return(

Welcome to Your Dashboard {props.name}

  • buttonController(e, "workouts")} href="#">Your Workouts
  • buttonController(e, "newWorkout")} href="#">New Workout
  • buttonController(e, "templates")} href="#">Your Templates
  • buttonController(e, "newTemplate")} href="#">New Template
) } export default Dashboard;
